    "## 4. Merging Datasets and Defining Heat Waves <a id='merge'></a>\n",
    "\n",
    "### Heat Wave Definition\n",
    "\n",
    "Following the **NOAA/NWS Excessive Heat** standard:\n",
    "\n",
    "> A **heat wave day** is any day within a run of at least **3 consecutive days** where TMAX >= 95 F (35 C).\n",
    "\n",
    "The 95 F threshold matches NWS Excessive Heat Warnings issued in the Dominion service territory.\n"
   ]
